Key Match Events: Bangladesh won by 25 runs against the Netherlands.
Shakib's classy half-century helped Bangladesh to 159-5.
Netherlands lost four middle-order wickets for six runs.
Engelbrecht gave the Netherlands hope with 33 off 22 balls.
Tim Pringle lost his leg stump to Taskin Ahmed.
Mustafizur Rahman bowled a brilliant 19th over, conceding only two runs off the bat.
Post-Match Reflections: Ryan ten Doeschate commented that Bangladesh got the job done but may struggle in the next level of competition.
Isabelle Westbury noted that the Netherlands' performance was disappointing and that Bangladesh would be feeling confident.
